---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Base64Tool from '../../components/tools/Base64Tool';

const title = "Free Base64 Encoder/Decoder - Encode and Decode Online | Utility Hub";
const description = "Encode text to Base64 or decode Base64 to text with our free online tool. Instant encoding and decoding with copy support.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical="/tools/base64-encoder-decoder">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Base64 Encoder/Decoder</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Encode text to Base64 format or decode Base64 back to text. Instant conversion with copy support.</p>
      <Base64Tool client:load />
      <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none mt-12">
        <h2>What is Base64?</h2>
        <p>Base64 is a binary-to-text encoding scheme that represents binary data in an ASCII string format. It's commonly used for transmitting data over media designed to handle text, such as email attachments and HTML form data.</p>
        <h2>How to Use</h2>
        <p>Select "Encode" to convert text to Base64, or "Decode" to convert Base64 back to text. Enter your input and click the convert button.</p>
        <h2>Use Cases</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email attachments:</strong> Encode binary files for email transmission</li>
          <li><strong>Data URIs:</strong> Embed images directly in HTML/CSS</li>
          <li><strong>API development:</strong> Encode binary data in JSON payloads</li>
          <li><strong>Web security:</strong> Basic authentication header encoding</li>
          <li><strong>Data transfer:</strong> Safely transmit binary data over text protocols</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Internal Links</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/tools/json-formatter">JSON Formatter</a> - Format JSON</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/jwt-decoder">JWT Decoder</a> - Decode JWT tokens</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/uuid-generator">UUID Generator</a> - Generate UUIDs</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/timestamp-converter">Timestamp Converter</a> - Convert timestamps</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/regex-tester">Regex Tester</a> - Test patterns</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Frequently Asked Questions</h4>
        <p>Question: Is Base64 encryption? Answer: No, Base64 is encoding, not encryption. It can be easily decoded by anyone.</p>
        <p>Question: Does Base64 make data smaller? Answer: No, Base64 increases data size by approximately 33%.</p>
        <p>Question: Is my data sent to a server? Answer: No, all encoding/decoding happens locally in your browser.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
</write_to_file>